***Attends Malam Adamu Adamu Daughter’s Wedding In Azare DAMATURU – Damagum, the headquarters of Fune Local Government Council, was full to brim on Saturday, when the Governor of Yobe state and Chairman APC Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee, Mai Mala Buni, today gave out the hands of the daughter of his Deputy, Fatima Idi Barde Gubana and received in marriage a wife for the Deputy Governor’s son, Hussaini Idi Barde Gubana. Similarly, the Emir of Fika and Chairman Yobe state Council of chiefs, Alh. Muhammadu Abali Ibn Muhammadu Idrissa, gave out the hands of another daughter of the Deputy Governor, Habiba Idi Barde Gubana to Gambo Usman. Aftermath Of Abia APC Chairman’s Death, Ex-bank Chief Emerges… Fayemi Expresses Fresh Concern Over Assaults On Uniformed Men In… The wedding was presided over by the Special Adviser to the Governor on Religious Affairs, Ustas Babagana Mallam kyari. The highly elated Governor, said “the large turn out of people to witness this wedding ceremony was an evident indication that peace has returned to Yobe state. “I thank the great honour done to me and my Deputy by honouring the invitation to grace this occassion. “I commend the people of Yobe state for their support and continuous prayers for the full return of peace to the state” Governor Buni said. He prayed for a successful and happy married life to the new couples. POLL Similarly, Governor Buni was in Azare, Bauchi State to witness the wedding fatiha of the daughter of Malam Adamu Adamu, the Hon. Minister of Education. The wedding was attended by Vice President Prof. Yemi Osibanjo, the Senate President Dr Ahmad Ibrahim Lawan, state governors, Ministers, Public officers and prominent politicians. Governor Buni enjoined Nigerians to always promote unity, peace and peaceful coexistence as reflected in the wedding ceremonies with Nigerians coming from all walks of life.